,Recommended,258970,12236821,"Posted: 25 September, 2014",all,bigdrip681,"Before you buy this game keep in mind: THIS IS CLASSIC ARCADE STYLE GAUNTLET. THIS IS NOTHING LIKE GAUNTLET DARK LEGACY.I have mixed feelings about this one. I am having a lot of fun with it playing it with friends, but I feel like they went so far trying to stay true to the Gauntlet formula that it feels downright unfair and frustrating at times. The biggest problem I have is Death, who pops up every other level, and kills you instantly if you get caught. There is no way to kill him, all you can do is run. I almost rage quit because he popped up directly over a turkey leg and killed me right as I ate it. So not only did I lose a life, but the food was wasted as well.Having said that, the combat is fun and really thrilling. It feels just like playing gauntlet in the arcade. Because you know you have limited lives and no auto health regen, there is a real feeling of failure and loss if you all die which makes it way more tense than a lot of ""modern"" games where you know ""Meh, if i die I just respawn and keep going"".Overall it is a decent enough time to recommend. If you are on the fence, wait till it goes on sale. It's definitely worth 10$, especially if you can find a couple friends to play with."
