,Recommended,258970,29424984,Posted: 22 January,all,nukem266,"nukes-viewHi all, nukes here.Gauntlet is a top down, dungeon crawler, which will have you hacking and slashing your way through hordes of enemies. Which sold it for me, who doesn't love running through dark dungeons slaughtering everything you are faced with.Based off of the original 1985 Gauntlet, this version captures its magic beautifully.Still offering four player co-operative locally and online as well. Gauntlet offers a story mode, Endless mode and a Coliseum. Each can be played with friends or on your own.I love this game, as it is easy to pick up and play, playing with friends made my experience even more fun. Although the community is not massive people still do play this online.The Game PlayBefore you jump into raid the dungeons in search of glorious riches. You are able to choose from four playable characters,with a fifth as DLC.Each with very different abilities and play styles.Warrior, Valkyrie, Elf, Wizard andNecromancer (DLC content)Personally my two favourite are the Valkyrie for mirror shield and clone combo, and the Wizard for his awesome spell combinations. Don't get me wrong though all the classes are brilliant.Personally Barbarian felt a little dumb and clumsy to me, Elf well his accent was just to annoying which really put me off his character.DifficultyThe difficulty of this game comes in three flavours.Unfortunately for all you hardcore gamers, as of Slayer edition, the fourth Unfair mode has been removed.With each increase in difficulty monsters have more hit points and run faster. Although more gold for all you looters.Easy - Says it all.Normal - Pretty much default.Hard -Well I am sure you get the point by now.Keep in mind the Colosseum mode the difficulty is fixed.Endless mode gradually increases as you make your way through the levels.(Keep in mind you don't keep gold form this mode, it is specifically for lives etc..)Controls & InterfaceThe controls are simple and easy to pick up, on original release the campaign had a tutorial,this helped with the wizard class.With Slayer edition release this has been removed. It is now in the form of aHow to Playpage on the main menu, which has controls laid out for each class.This game can be played with keyboard and mouse or a controller making sure you activate the controller before starting the game.Personally I found this game is more suited for controller use, especially with the wizard class.AchievementsThis game has achievements, some of them a fairly straight forward but even now I still haven't got to wave 50 on Endless or killed 15000 Orks.... Hurray for me.Unfortunately some of them are a grind.StoryThe campaign is based on going deeper through a series dungeons to challenge yourself, looting as you go. To find three pieces of sword for a sketchy wizard, on this Gauntlet journey you will encounter many deaths.Once you have completed a map(challenge)you are able to freely navigate to old and new missions plus bonus ones.Combat System, Skills & TraitsThe combat is fairly straight forward, swing here swing there, heads fall offGood ol mash the A button for best results.Least from a Barbarian or Valkyrie's point of view or for Wizard and Elf you use the right analogue to fire your bow or burn, zap and freeze.This game can be fast paced and chaotic at times, keep yourself moving or knowing your choke points will keep you alive. It is easy to lose your character in the commotion.Especially playing with others.Since Slayer edition release the skills and abilities have changed, now equipment you buy will determine what moves and skills you have.Personally why they decided to change it is beyond me, I loved that the items were more cosmetic based.They also removed the perk system for masteries, which again is beyond me completely. As masteries, other than boasting rights are pretty much useless now.Sounds & EffectsSounds decent and fitting for dungeon scene. Although very loud on start up so remove your headset or be deafened.Some of the voice acting can be a bit much.GraphicsThe graphics settings are straight forward, this game is not to demanding although later levels on Endless mode could cause issues for lower spec'd machines.Gore can be turned off for the younger audiences.Humour & TriviaDefinitely a love hate relationship with the voice acting on this game, although humorous to a degree I cannot stand the Elf's strong accent.MultiplayerThis multiplayer on this game works well, as mentioned before can be done locally on a decent sized screenor you will lose your character a lot.Or can be done online with friends or strangers.I have never had problems finding a Story or Endless mode game, although keep in mind if you are joining someone else's game you may not have choice of your favourite character.Multiplayer is stable and I have never had connection issues unless host is in a distant country. If you are unsure just host your own.Story mode progress is saved whether you do it multi or single player.Bugs -ImportantI don't think I came across any game breaking bugs. Only annoyance is I mentioned before, is about starting the game after you turn on or connect your controller as sometimes Gauntlet may not pick it up.ConclusionOverall I found this game very fun to play, par some of the changes to Slayer Editionif you are buying it now you will never know what you have missed so this won't affect you. Although don't get me wrong the additions were great as well.I still play to get last achievements to this day, but I have had many hours of dying to hordes of enemies with friends and strangers.I personally hope they make another Gauntlet down the line sometime with even more content.I felt this game did do the originals games justice and I hope you will feel the same way.Because who doesn't like throwing explosive crates/barrels at their friends.Hope I helped.ηυĸєΜ266"
