,Not Recommended,258970,12216889,"Posted: 24 September, 2014",all,The Root Of All Evil,"There's something wrong with this game - and I'm still not sure what it is.Is it well-balanced, fun? YepNow that's out of the way - there's a few very odd design decisions.In putting in the ubiquitous levelling up, story, background and achievements, they've missed something of the original and the sequels - its ""open world"" feel. All of the dungeons are built to a very specific standard and focus you tightly down the next ""surprise"". Even if that's not explained to you what the surprise is - three times I had to return to the hub purely because I'd not done what the designer expected me to.It feels very much like a 2010 game in that all of your choices are made for you and drilled in from the start. There's no discovery curve as sort, just a line of achievements that act as little red ticks from the teacher.Saying that, it's still fun - all of the characters have a different style, the key sound is there - but it's definitely lost some of its charm. DEATH is now an enviromental hazard, Ghosts are now missiles of a sort; and it's set around Boss Monsters rather than Hordes - like every other game.7/10 - Treading the same old path rather than creating a new style.minus another point until they fix issues like swapping characters between games, swapping screen size and swapping keyboard controls. It will get a recommended when that's fixed."
,Not Recommended,258970,12211986,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,Doomkitten!,"This game is incredibly fun if you play it with a group of friends. The gameplay has just enough to it to keep it interesting in ways other than just a simple 8-way shooter, while remaining comfortably familiar to anyone that's ever played the classic Gauntlet games.  With friends, it's a fabulous romp that's well worth the admission fee.However... How did anyone miss the glaring obvious ""Elf can run AND shoot"" imbalance?  The usual ""the other classes have different strengths"" argument will come out, which might be true, but the elf can run, attack AND still be picking up all the gold while every other class has to choose between fighting and looting.   Unfortunately, with the end level 'scores' active, it is a poor thing to have as wildly an imbalancing play option as that.Hopefully it will improve, because right now I'm not pleased with the open multiplayer balance.  Any competent Elf (that plays selfishly, as the game seems to intend) will make every other player feel like their time spent playing was wasted.  That's a real shame on this otherwise good game.If you play solo, or with a group of cool people on regular occasions, then consider this a recommended game. Otherwise... I cannot recommend this game simply because of this imbalance issues."
