,Recommended,258970,14515470,"Posted: 17 February, 2015",all,Allison! [deaf],"Reviews for the Deaf and Hard of HearingOverall Rating: 8/10Gameplay Rating: 8/10Accessibility Rating: 9/10NotesOverall rating is a combination of the gameplay (mechanics and story) and accessibility (how the game includes deaf/hoh gamers).If you disagree with my take on the game or if something is factually incorrect, please leave a comment below!General GameplayGauntlet is a single player or co-op experience!  This tribute to the older games in its lineage reawakens the fun, top-down dungeon crawling, horde-destroying genius of the original games.Though a bit linear and slightly redundant, Gauntlet is still entertaining in both single and co-op modes.  The Colosseum mode brings together 4 players in classic arcade fashion.The achievements in Gauntlet come for both good and bad events, such as collecting gold or dying, and all make your character just a little better.ReplayabilityAs a co-op game with friends, however, Gauntlet's outstanding history shines through and the game becomes fun, amusing, and challenging.Additional replayability comes from trying to complete the game and all achievements with all of the character types.  If you're a completionist, you may enjoy trying to get this one done.  Just bring a friend!General AccessibilityAccessibility OptionsGauntlet has sound settings controls for master volume, music, effects, and dialogue, as well as captions (subtitles).When you start the game, it goes straight to the main menu, so you can set captions on before any events happen.For gamers with mobility issues, Gauntlet's primary controls are game controller, but it works with keyboard and mouse just as well.  All keys can be rebound to suit your needs.Subtitles & CaptionsCaptions in Gauntlet are great!  Gauntlet is not a very dialogue-rich game, so most of what is said is flavor text, but it all seems to be there.Pros:- Captions for characters are colored according to that character's color (green for elf, for example), and captions from the evil mastermind leading the gauntlet are white.- Captions are easy to read in large font across the bottom of the screen.Cons:- Captions do not indicate who is speaking by name.  Only a *minor* problem because they are colored.Chatting/CommunicatingGauntlet supports in-game chat and colors text according to which character you're playing.---Visit Games Reviews for the Deaf/HoHhttp://steamcommunity.com/groups/gamereviewsforthedeaf"
