,Recommended,258970,13080827,"Posted: 25 November, 2014",all,bT*Akira,"The original version of this game was a bit lackluster. After a couple years away from the game I decided to come back and see if anyone else played a game that I didn't recommend.What I came back to was a much improved game. The levels, the way you select which level you play, down to how you play each character greatly improved. I feel what I originally played was an early access game that was not listed as an early access.The game now feels polished, its solid all around and there are still active players. There is even a DLC to unlock a brand new playable character.You can play in campaign mode and go through the story and play each scripted level, earning gold and upgrading your characters gear along the way. You can go back and play any level you have played, as long as you've beaten it on that difficulty. There are three difficulties that ramp up appropriately. Easy is good for one player, any skilled player can get through a majority of the levels without needing help of others. On normal you will want at least two players, if not three. On Hard difficulty you want four players; three can be done, but four is SO much better.There is an endless mode in which some levels you see in the campaign, along with others, are randomly loaded with enemies and events. Money you earn can be used to buy food, potions or skull coins (1-ups essentially). Some levels in endless are very easy, simple. Others are loaded with lots and lots of hard enemies in one locked room.Between the two modes, and a coloseum mode that I have not played, I have to recommend this game. Buy it now while there are still players! Othersie you will need three other players to play with you either in  local multiplayer, online, or a mix of both."
76561198123513396,Not Recommended,258970,24551975,"Posted: 27 July, 2016",all,maddpsyintyst,"While this game resembles Gauntlet games in a superficial way, it doesn't really play like a classic Gauntlet game.  At best, this is either a game inspired by Gauntlet, or a clone of Gauntlet, but in my opinion isn't truly worthy of the name.I'll start by building on the clone-of-Gauntlet idea.  In my opinion, there are games older than this one that play better and look better.  Either of the Torchlight games, and by extension the second Diablo game (which is the only one of those that I played, TBH), are good examples.  Also, any of the Baldur's Gate or Icewind Dale games, as well as Temple of Elemental Evil and Pool of Radiance, would work (I might add that ToEE and PoR were panned pretty badly at the time, too).  Even the older versions of Gauntlet are better and even more immersive than this.On a related and not-so-minor note, this game is choppy even at the lowest graphic settings.  This is simply unacceptable, when so many clones of clones of games coming out these days (especally on the pay-to-win platforms like Android) seem to emphasize graphics over gameplay and content.The keyboard controls are goofy and inconsistent among the characters.  I could probably get used to using WSAD-style controls on this game, except that there are only four directions to move.  Again, so many other games trump this by default.  If that isn't bad enough, the wizard has a completely different set of controls to get used to (except for movement), compared to the others.  Couldn't the wizard have been made to play closer to the other character types, rather than awkwardly fumbling through different spell schools?  Worse yet, the controls are not customizable at all.  I didn't try using my controller to see if the experience is better, because I lost interest in the game content and graphics too soon."
