76561198046733827,Recommended,258970,12430952,"Posted: 9 October, 2014",all,BenWalmsley,"I've been seeing a lot of mixed reviews regarding the content of this game.  As a hardcore Gauntlet II (1989) NES fan, this game is meant to be casually played in a room full of friends, ideally with a few beers and pizzas.  It was not meant to be a multiplayer Skyrim.  As someone who has personally put many hours into this game with 4-players on local co-op, this game is now my ""Hammerwatch party"" replacement, and i love every minute of it.  If you want a game to play with friends when they come over, do yourself a favor and get a few usb controllers and it will be an absolute blast.  The repetition is not what i would call a downfall, for it is what always made this series.  It encourages cooperation and trial-and-error whenever a poorly-planned mob-filled LEEROY JENKINS room becomes a massacre.  And for me personally, it's pretty hilarious when your party gets mobbed like King Joffery in the streets of Flea Bottom, even if you and all your friends end up dying.TL:DR version: Red Warrior shot the food.  Buy the damn game."
