,Recommended,258970,12212222,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,Xifurez,"This version of Gauntlet is an ode to the original arcade and NES versions of Gauntlet. It feature the four heroes from the originals with the respected colors. It holds the classic arcade style hack and slash that inspired games like Diablo, with the additive of armor and relics that give the game a little bit more depth and a sense of progression. Ontop of that each character has it's own unique feel and move set, not a single character is alike in this game and it gives a very unique challenge of overcoming each stage with certain limits and abilities. It does not have many levels, but you will find that is because you build up in difficulty through them, starting in normal to unlock your first armor pieces that you will use to complete the levels in hard more, and so forth. As it is right now it has a ton of replayability and is very fun for multiplayer. There are not many levels in the base but for an asking price of 15 dollars you really get your moneys worth, and hopefully future DLC will add more levels and armor to the game.All in all I give this version of Gauntlet a 8/10. It's got rather well placed music, a very decent challenge even on normal difficulties and a nice sense of progression."
