,Recommended,258970,12214013,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,Jareth Gawain,"Luckily, I had the day off from work today, and got to spend pretty much the entire day playing the remake of one of my favorite classic games, Gauntlet. Arrowhead did a superb job from what I've seen so far. The graphics aren't anything phenomenal, nonetheless, the game looks pretty good and runs smooth. The gameplay is fast paced and well fleshed out. Playing online with random players is just as brutal as you would expect from a new age remake of Gauntlet. You don't always feel like your party members are your friends. If feels like you and 3 other heroes are just trying to survive the death trap you've been thrown into, and you can either help each other, or take what you can for yourself. This can be frustrating but also extremely fun. It adds an element to the game that is Gauntlets signiature and they did a great job resurrecting this classic, adding modern features without subtracting from the old school arcade feel. They added masteries and relics, which is the closest thing to ""leveling up""the game has. So over time your characters will get a bit stronger. But still, DO NOT get this game if you want just like to grind. You won't be building an immortal barbarian with super l33t gear in this game.  If you aren't bringing some effort and skill to the game, you will die. It's best played with at least 2 or more people, but solo can be fun as well.   I do think theres some balancing that needs to be done, and I'd like to see more levels added in the near future, but as of now it is totally worth 20$."
,Recommended,258970,12214047,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,nsc,"This is nothing like any gauntlet game I've ever played.It's like those Marvel top down beat 'em up games from the ps2/gamecube era.Lots of button mashing, lots of grunts to kill, lots of different ways to do it.I love the game but I think that the classes are poorly balanced, but since it's a co-op that doesn't matter too much.I like how ""achievements"" unlock skills and abilities, probably the only time I care about achievements haha.I highly reccomend this game if you like top down beat 'em ups with SOLID controls. They're flawless.Warrior:Plays like he should, press the X X X and the Y Y Y. His B spin attack is invincible and gives you some extra range. I dislike how you have to charge his charge, but the charge jump attack is good even if it takes a bit of practice to get the range right. His heavy attack deals a LOT of damage, very useful.Valkyrie:I like her dash attack more than warrior's bull run (although I like the warrior's bull run) her shield doesn't seem that useful since hordes are usually how you die, but she does a good job of being different than the warrior so kudos.Archer:Easily the most broken of the classes, his bombs, rolls, and power shots are incredible. It doesn't take long to learn how to massacre monsters with archer, but there is a bit of a skill cap so he's not entirely braindead (just monstly brain dead)Wizard:I hope you liked magika because this guy is magika as ♥♥♥♥. Good luck using him. He's easily my favourite to play as but he is by far the hardest class to play. He has a TON of spells and they all have individual cool downs so poppin' off damage can be easy, but you're going to need to memorize all the spell inputs before you can even be mediocre at wizard.All in all the game is really fun and I hope you guys check it out and enjoy it."
