,Recommended,258970,12226032,"Posted: 24 September, 2014",all,Joneko Joestar,"Some people are being very misleading about characters being super unbalanced and only one class being viable when I think that is the farthest thing from the truth. So here is my quick Definition of each character and their ROLES.WARRIOR- Warrior is the nistalgic class of beat'em up with the mantra that, ""a good defence is having everyone around you die before you do"". All his attacks are melee with only a charge up dash for means to escape. Overall The Warrior is meant to be in the middle of action while yelling, ""I HAVE THE POWWWWWERRRRRR!!!!""Abilities- Attack, Heavy attack, Spin attack(only ability wth a cool down), charge run.VALKYRIE- Is the class That I have heared being called the better warrior, or Over Powered, or Easy mode. 'Tis true she is easy but that is only because she has the most resources that take smaller interactions but higher persistance.Example; Valkyrie has 3 combat moves that make her very agile with disposing of small creatures, and 1 defensive measure that can make her a stand alone immoble but invunerable tank. She can hack at enemies swiftly, throw her sheild and not block for a very short time but do a lot of damage to multiple people, and she has a dash attack that kills smaller creatures instantly and still does a fair amount of damage to things not executed by it. This dash does have prep and recovery frames but no cooldown really. One can abuse it to fly through easier levels, but once you step up the difficulty her role is not the 'no sweat' offence based character portrayed by other people. Once her dash cant solve many of her own problems, her blocking skill comes into play. She has the ability to Block all damage with this sheild as long as she hold the block button toward the source of damage and even minorly hurt smaller enemies and reflect projectiles. In a true team situation she is the single mother (and only women) of the team. Keeping her children from harm while paving a path for them for safe passage. She is a GardianWIZARD- The wizard is so fun in this game. He has 9 different spells he can use with no mana costs and all spells having separate cooldown timers. You input the spells by tapping 2 spell buttons in any order. I play with a 360 controller so I have X Y and B to make all my spells. Their are spells like fireball which is a small fast firing fireball, Ice ray fires a small low damage beam of ice to slow any one who touches it and damages them slowly, to spells like Flame serpant that sends yourself flying accrose the screen as a living flame that makes you almost invunerable and sets fire to all who touches you. The Wizard has a spell for all conditions as long as you know all spell cominations (a liitle difficult to master); however, he has very litttle health and has no true basic attack. All of your preformance is up to you picking the right spells from the 3 buttons input system. His true role can be anywhere from a high Artillery and AOE ( area of effect ) to a more support type of a class because he can make barriers and slow down a whole pocket of enemies with or completely freeze a small group. (3 spells i did not define)Shock Barrier- a barrier that repels most enimies and destroys projectileFreeze Blast- a small blast freezing enemiesFrost Grenade- a ball that exploads a small distance away and slows all enemies in the radius greatly(P.S this names of these spells are not official but what i refer to them as, sorry for my lack of knowledge)ALL SPELLS- Ice beam, fireball, shock barrier, freeze blast, big fireball/mortar, chain lightning, frost grenade, thunder punch, firedash/flame serpantARCHER- or the adventurer as he calls himself, The Archer is the most under appreciated class in the whole game. The archer is know for as that guy who is faster than everyone else and takes all the gold and does no damage. LIES!! ALLL LIES! The Archer has a very unique role in this game that not man people realize to its full potential. He is an assassin. many people are probably thinking, ""HOW CAN HE ASSASSINATE ANYTHING WITH NO DAMAGE?!?!?!""shut up voices in my head, let me talk. The Archers kit makes him the most mobile and slippery player in this game.His kit consists ofFiring arrows- who would of guest it, the cant damage spawners but they can take out plenty of enemies quicklyCharge shot- Charge an arrow to get the farthest ranged attack in the game and do good damageBomb- Lay down a bomb with good AOE and good damageDive Role- Role a short distance away, can go through targets, very short cooldownBombshot- later in the game you get this ability and it mix's charge shot and bomb to create a explosive bolt that sticks to walls or enemiesROLE OF ARCHER CONTINUED- so with all of these abilities yes he does takes gold because he's faster but think of him as a hitman. He has precise skills to take out thos enemies that do way too much damage from way too far away. and like an assassin he goes into danger ( Diving; something you cant do without dying ) and kills things that are unreachable to you. Every Assassin has a price though, some are just douchier than others and take EVERYTHING.... but then again this is still a gauntlet gameOVERALL- this game is a blast of nistalgia with a hint of something new ( an interactive rewarding combat system ). I think it is soooooooo worth playing! And like all Gauntlet games the more friends that play with you, the more fun you can have.For a Re-Boot-10/10OVERALL REGRETS- accidently bought 2 conditioners instead of 1 shampoo and 1 conditioner... poop"
