,Recommended,258970,12214307,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,undisputedloser,"I admit I was skeptical about this one. Recent entries in the series haven't done well. Legends and Dark Legacy were pretty bad. I wasn't sure they'd be able to pull this one off, but they did.This is a solid game that stands well on it's own. I'm not saying it's perfect, as there are some quirks and rough edges. There's a strange 1920x1080 screen resolution bug (check the Steam guides for that work around). I think the way it visually tracks progress towards acheivements is confusing and unintuitive. These are things that should definitely be fixed, but nothing I would consider gamebreaking.If you're a fan of the series, especially 80's arcade machines or the original NES version, this is a must-have. The developers went back to the roots of the series and on the things that makes Guantlet unique: monster generators, destructible food, the iconic announcer. They built new features on top of that like elemental spell combinations for the wizard, and the valkyrie's flying shield. They added an item system that lets you customize the characters accoring to your playstyle. But it all feels grounded in the original game, like it should have been there already.If you're a fan of Guantlet, or just like killing mobs with 3 of your closest friends (or random strangers for that matter), it's worth picking up."
