76561197970439755,Recommended,258970,12224892,"Posted: 24 September, 2014",all,Silent-Strike,"You know I absolutely LOVED the arcade and N64 versions of Gauntlet so I'm bias as far as that goes but I really have to say that day one bugs really turn me off.  Strike one for this company was the ungodly frustrating bugs in Magicka.  This is strike two for Arrowhead Game Studios and if the Gauntlet bugs aren't seriously addressed in later releases, they've lost a customer for life.FAIR WARNING:  I'm writing this review with 1.6hrs of gameplay under my belt so draw your own conclusions on what I noticed during my brief time.  In complete honesty, after the game crashed 1.6hrs in, I didn't bother loading it up again and played Civ 5 instead.  I'm really irked about my ill-Magicka feelings bleeding through onto this review, but that's what happens when you don't address defects in your software.Pros: Nostalgia, graphics, puzzle environment, online multiplayer, levels load very fast.Cons: oh boy, here we go...-Full screen video.  The game start with your windows start bar displaying.  You can change it to full screen but the full screen setting doesn't always stick.-Games in Progress:  You can't join (or have your friends join) a game that has already started. Highly annoying.-Character Selection: You can't select more than one character type at the same time.  i.e. you can't have four warriors at the same time.  You should be able to have a red/blue/green/yellow warrior but you no can haz!-Upon death: I would love to have the ability to change character classes but since I'm locked to one class once I join the game, I can't do that.-The camera.  I played with two other players and all of us were on the same half of the screen, yet, the camera doesn't move to compensate unless you touch the edge of the screen.  This leads you to burn up keys that you've collected.-Auto Fire:  When using the mouse, you can hold the left click to auto-fire with the archer, but none of the other characters have an auto-fire ability.  This leads to insane amounts of clicking and can get really tiresome.  I haven't tested this with my USB Logitech selectable auto-fire controller but I'm going to be forced to use it if this feature doesn't get added.-Buggy:  Random crashes reminiscent of Magicka that turned you off to Magicka in the first place.  I was lucky enough to get to unlock level 4 with two of my friends in one sitting before the first crash occurred.-Collision:  Collision should be an option to be turned on or off.  It's upsetting when your friend blocks a doorway and you die because can't get past him.-Random spawn timers:  I've died and have had to wait anywhere from 5 seconds to 20 seconds to spawn and have no idea why the timers are different.-Wizard:  The gameplay is challenging enough as it is, and your character is already always on the move dodging enemies, so why introduce ""Magicka style"" 3 or 4 button combinations needed to cast a magic spell?  It's my opinion that the wizard will be the least used character because of this.-Warrior and Valkyrie:  The HP attributes on these two characters needs to be improved, either that or make the fighting space a lot larger, have have the baddies do less damage, or introduce a slight knock back on every attack.Hopefully these issues will be addressed in future updates."
