76561198070413486,Recommended,258970,12219343,"Posted: 24 September, 2014",all,RonEmpire,"Score:  8 / 10Fun game overall.    Nice Dungeon crawler experience.   I like the sound of the potion and the music of the game. Has the Gauntlet vibe.  Killing stuff and picking up powerups potions,keys,gold, food like an arcarde game.My complaints:#1   NO KEYBINDING.   If you choose keyboard mode, you're forced to their control scheme.   Some of the characters the default is okay.   But the defensive action button being Left keyboard shift key is just awful.  My left hand pinky finger is just not reactive/responsive enough to reach that far and press it.   (small hands).The worst is the Wizard.   ""Wizard NEEDS keybinding badly!""  - The wizard basically has a bunch of spells that require you to do key/mouse button combinations.    And the combinations are very difficult to do and often times conflict.   They should have allowed these to be just number keys that conjure the spells.  Or at the very least  allow for 'secondary key' bindings like left mouse button = 1 key.  right mouse buntton = 2 key.   shift key = 3 key.   So we can press the numbers to create the combos.I have not tried controller pad mode.  But there are no options in the settings to go back to choosing which input controls.  You get presented keyboard or controller.    Choose wisely!   (otherwise, you might have to muck with deleting external files or delete game and reinstall).#2  LOCKED CURSOR to game window bug.Playing the game on windowed mode, has some major buggy cursor issues.    When I want to 'alt tab' away from the game window as my focus.  The cursor STILL locks me into the square window bounding box.  Even when I trying to do things from other windows.   For example, trying to use my web browser it won't let me move my mouse freely in my web browser but locks me into an area of the browser.     Needless to say, if you need to do something alt tabbed in another window or your desktop you have to quit the game.    Can't even move the game window.   So if the game launched and you had it moved to the far left or the right of the monitor.   You can't move it back to the center.#3 No Endless Dungeon mode.The game basically plays like Diablo 3 - Greater Rifts.  You go through one of the 12 doors from the game hub.  Which is basically the same as a ""Town"" with a ""Vendor"".       Each of the 12 doors has only 4 maps(aka levels).    So go through 1 door, you are presented with a map can be maze like with rooms like zelda 1 underground dungeon. or can be a single room with just waves of monsters. or a single boss room.   This really doesn't play much like the old gauntlet game at all. Adding in these jumping square platforms.The players health does NOT decrease like the old school version, where you have that urgency to find food or finish the map to go to the next map.    Instead it has a death guy chasing after you on some of the maps. Which is not too bad.  But just FYI, incase people were wondering if the health decreases or not.Finishing a door, takes you back to the ""hub"" or ""town"".   Which is similar to Diablo 3.  You finish a Rift, that door is done. You can go back if you want.    So it's the same as diablo. repeating the levels.What I do like:The vendor sells you only 4 items (relics) and you can upgrade them  and use only 2 out of the 4.    Which I like the feature.  Since it lets you decide which of the 2 to use for strategies.   And he sells you cosmetic items (like Diablo transmog).I hope the fix the 3 complaints.   So I'd give this game a 6/10."
