,Recommended,258970,12227051,"Posted: 24 September, 2014",all,OliverQueen,"Let me first start off with a quick pointer to those of you who have an issue with this game starting in the taskbar and not being able to open the window: You need to go into your Steam folder, then steamapps, then common folder. Locate the Gauntlet Folder and open it. Go into the Contents folder and locate the settings. Open with a text editor (Wordpad is fine) look for the line that says Fullscreen = False, and change that to Fullscreen = True. Save and exit the editor. If it still gives you problems, hit Alt-Tab. That's what worked for me.Despite the above inconveniece. I am really enjoying the game. I chose to play as the Valkyire, and she is a blast to play. In the beginning, you'll get to try each class before the game actually starts. Wizard is very interesting actually, but will be the hardest class to play as. I wouldn't recommend that anyone use him for single player. The Warrior is the most well rounded character, the Valkyrie is the defensive character, and has some of the best abilities in the game, and the Elf is a very fast range character, but his attacks are very weak.Each class has their own special abilities. Warrior can spin attack and rush, Valkyrie can charge thrust and block with her shield as well as throw it, Elf can use his bombs and roll abillity, and the wizard can mix elements for various spells. Added to these abilities are relics which you can buy between levels, which consist of three floors. The relic uses are limited to the amount of potions you have. Think of the potions as MP, they are NOT health.Level design is okay. I don't expect anything special from dungeon crawlers since the main action here is hack and slash. It does seem like you see a lot of the same things in the ""procedurely generated"" levels. You have to get through those levels quickly though, so you may not notice it right away. I started noticing it on the second floor.I like the retro sounds for picking up the items like potions and keys. It's a great throwback to the original arcade game. Other than that, there's not much talk about in terms of music or sound. Everything is pretty generic there. The graphics are not bad for the type of game this is, but they're not stellar.Multiplayer is great, and this allows for local co-op which is a rarity these days. I'd really recommend that you play with friends though; it's sometimes hard to get a group due to players dropping out in the lobby. This is likely because only one person can play each class.  If you can find a group, it's a blast.It's not for everyone, but Gauntlet is a fun dungeon crawler to be enjoyed either way you play; with friends or by yourself, but the real fun comes in when you have 3 other people to play with.DON'T SHOOT THE FOOD! I'm looking at you QUESTOR, THE ELF!"
