76561198074461797,Recommended,258970,13632366,"Posted: 27 December, 2014",all,Vonstyne,"Verdict: 7 / 10The 1980’s Gauntlet characters return in this new era of gaming: Thor the warrior, Thyra the valkyrie, Merlin the wizard and Questor the elf. Each one having their own progression called masteries. As you chop down, skewering, obliterating or sniping foes, the character becomes stronger overtime, even awarded in death too! Relics, a new feature, activated by potions, have different effects on oneself or enemies. Having it on the right the character can make all the difference in heat of battle. The voice acting is a neat touch and nicely done for the characters to feel more lively, especially Questor’s having a Scottish accent.Unfortunately, the biggest letdown of the game is the length… it’s short. Finished roughly about five hours on the second hardest difficulty. After completing the game, the repetitiveness is harsh because you’ll be playing the same dungeons again, again and again. At that point, you’ll be increasing the character’s masteries. Still, it declines interest and the replay value quite fast.The developers no less stuck true to the 1980’s Gauntlet feel. With its amount of content and shortness of the game, it’s going to be hard to love the game. I still recommend the game if your looking for some good old hack ‘n’ slash cooperative fun.And remember… don’t destroy the food."
