,Recommended,258970,33909916,Posted: 30 July,all,Nicholas,"On the surface this game appeared like it was nothing more than a cheap game made to cash in on an older more famous license, but after playing it I can say that in my opinion it's a very high quality product, and a genuinely fun game.By setting your match to Public it's easy enough to get grouped up with some people, you may not always be doing the exact mission you want if you don't host, but playing with people is what makes this game fun and it hasn't been difficult to do so.The missions themselves seem to vary a lot in length and difficulty, without much sense of a precise progression...but the game is fun and rewarding enough to simply hop into a session and grind some levels out for gold or to help someone with their progression.My biggest complaint is that even after you accrue gold it just never feels like there is a ton of upgrades to buy for your character. You never really get the sense of being that much more strong or powerful by the end of the game, and your left slot is essentially useless because of how sparingly the tokens are given out for using that power. As far as I can tell after you've bought a couple upgrades the only thing to spend your money on is gear, but it wouldn't appear to enhance you in any way and seems to be purely cosmetic.So on the positive side, lots of fun coop action, and the gameplay/presentation all feel high quality and well made. The downside is just not a lot of depth to the progression.Would recommend, even if you don't have friends who play you can surely find some random people online to join you."
