,Recommended,258970,12210101,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,Kane Reynolds,"Sadly, the original version of this game didn’t get a full year before it got its upgrade, but it’s not without its charm. Essentially it is the same game as when it was released but a few tweaks and minor issues fixed, as well as a few added.The original HUB where you chose levels is now fixed so the Host is the one who picks instead of everyone running around trying to play their favorite level over and over.There’s now a mode called Endless where bad guys come in large waves and each level gets harder. I made it to level 30 before we got overrun and ran out of tokens. This mode is kind of cool because your gold outside the mode isn’t used for purchases, instead the gold you collect as you go is the only gold you get so fighting over the crown becomes crucial. You can also buy skull tokens for lives, potions, and food at the start of each floor. My advice, buy skull tokens any time you can – you will need them and they aren’t offered on every floor.By far the biggest overhaul to the gameplay at least that I saw was the reconstruction of Relic items; they don’t use potions anymore and instead use a cooldown mechanic. Talisman items are what old Relics were and require potions to use and they still have the same flaw in that if people don’t have a Talisman and pick up a potion the potion is used up and forfeit. I guess it’s a fair deal considering we have cooldown abilities now.Characters now have abilities unique to their weapon choice. The Warrior’s hammer can do the spin attack it was known for or can create a powerful shockwave. The Valkyrie can call down lightning or throw her shield like Captain America. And the Wizard has invisibility and hellfire abilities. The Necromancer can choose skeleton warrior, archer, or ghosts as her minions. Best addition so far.Enemies got an overhaul too and aside from different models here’s what I’ve seen so far:-Zombie giants have a bit more health and can pop up at random, so look for coffins.-Zombie champions come in shield and archer variant and have faster rush abilities and can call down ice arrows. A nice addition for some challenge.-Necromancers can now come in two-stage fights, kind of like a mini boss. One fight will be their mortal form and the other in their ghost form which changed very little.The first boss didn’t change at all, but now you can fight zombie giants during his fight.-Grunts look different and can be empowered by the Shaman.-Shaman look different and now shoot bolts of green that break off and turn into more bolts rather than the skull that follows you around like in the original version.-Giant Orcs can break their hammers and charge. Watch out.-New Minions: Spider soldiers. They are smaller version of Spider queens but can’t do much damage and can be stun-locked.-Spider queens look different and seem to have a little more health but no real change.-The second boss had more lighting added to the level. Thank you.-Cultist that turned into demon in the original version now explode when they die, sending purple bolts in a four-way patter. Watch out.-The cult leader got a new look and his sparkly bolt thing seems to be pretty inaccurate. Okay.-Basic demons gave the lion share of the update and can now stun lock enemies, and look different. Really watch out.That’s what I got so far. I haven’t gotten too far yet.Unfair mode is gone now and I say good riddance. It was nice unlocking certain masteries quicker but I hated being reminded I needed food when there was no food in the level. Stay dead and buried, unfair mode.Armor and weapons don’t need to be unlocked by beating certain levels in higher difficulties, now they can just be bought, which is okay I guess.All and all I like it and still recommend it. I play both single player and multiplayer.Pros- Cooldown abilities give the game a nice customization tool and good feel to gameplay.- Endless Mode for those brave enough to venture into the deep of the game.- Connection issues seemed to get a big fix. Big plus in my book.Meh- Some level layouts remain the same – some good, some still needing work.- During the Lobby scene people can put the Ready screen in an endless lobby hitting Ready/Not Ready and resetting the 30 second timer.- You can just buy the armor now instead of having to unlock it.Cons- Masters redone – abilities like less damage from the Valkyrie, coming back to life as Necromancer, and Warrior Regeneration are gone. No damage bonuses for killing so many of one foe.- Some items are still pretty worthless."
