76561198009558464,Recommended,258970,12208981,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,[T]orus[B]east,"Takes me back several years.  Still feels very much like the original with a slight twist. The relics are nice, even if I am hesitant to buy any as I don't know which are best.  But The armor is also nice, nothing is givne to you and it all must be earned within the gauntlet.  The perk system is nice too.  You can gain perks from death and just about everything else.  These perks are minor but for sure make for a easier gameplay the more you get.The competitive feel of this game is top notch.  I find myself scrambling for gold, potions, and crowns before my teammates so that I can be rewards well and be able to buy upgraded relics, armor, etc...  It makes me consider if I should steal/destroy that food or let the teammate who is 5% health have it, knowing he's been grabbing a lot of the gold in a level.  By letting a teammate die they drop a small portion of the gold they have collected and you are allowed to pick it up.  Down side is if you do this to often your teammate will catch on and begin stealing food from you as well.The over all game play feels nice, and mouse and keyboard are adopted to the game very well.  As far as classes go Valky, Wizard, and Ranger are all about equal with their own strengths and weaknesses.  The warrior however seems very lack luster.  With a charge that has to charge up for about .75 seconds and low durabilty (from what is seems), he can't really take a beating though he is required to be in the fray of fighting. Valky, brings a melee style play to the game with a bit more durability and even some range.  She can shield to block attacks and with her shield throw can handle 2 halves of a room at once.  The archer, though limited range is very adept at staying just out of range of enemies while still staying relevant in the fight. The wizard is a more technical class and casts spells depending on what button combos you press to ready his next spell with.  But is very strong range damage.I have just scratched the surface of this game and I look forward to diving deeper into the game in the following days and weeks.  4 out of 5 stars, due to the grindy feel and warrior being a lack luster choice in comparison to the other classes."
