,Recommended,258970,12280099,"Posted: 28 September, 2014",all,Deep,"Plays like the classic Guantlet game with newer graphics and effects.   It can be fun and enjoyable.  I prefer playing as the wizard, because I like the variety.  Some people like the warrior, because he's basically a hack and slash character.  The other two are sort of middle of the road characters.  The game doesn't have that many levels though, and it's lacking a few features that would make it the best Guantlet game ever created.   Here's the bad:- Screen is shared like in other Guantlet games, and that can be annoying when someone will not move and you can't proceed to the next area.  Some people don't care about this, but I do.  I think it would be a far better game if each player had their own screen.- No voice or text chat at the time of this review.  You only have emotes, and that can suck since you can't really communicate with other players and meet other people who enjoy the game.- No browsing for a game, so you'll only be able to join a random game, and sometimes it tells you the game if full, or that you joined a game already in progress and so you must go back and click to find another.  Why can't I just join a game in progress?  Nothing is more annoying than playing with 4 people, one or two quit, and no one can join!  You have to go back to lobby and wait for another random person to come in.  Oh, and there's no lobby chat either.-  No key rebinding so you have to use the default controls.  The devs have promised they are adding this ability in the near future.  Still, it should have been something that was put into the game by release, but I got to hand it to them that they have responded to this request.  Well, hopefully they will.-  Steam doesn't appear to be fully integrated.  What I mean by this, is that there is no way to shift tab and look at who you are playing with and easily send a friend request.   At least if they had this fully integrated, you could easily friend people and group chat on steam.Overall it's a rather short game, but with some replayability.  I like the idea that there are way to level up your character, collect gold and buy upgrades.  But what would be nice is a randomly generated dungeon and perhaps endless dungeon mode, and I have read (but not a 100% sure) that the devs are planning on adding this to the game in a future patch (whenever that will be).Though it has it's shortcomings, I am enjoying playing it.  So I'd recommend it.  It certainly isn't as complex as Magicka, but then neither was the classic Guantlet game that I was a huge fan of back in the day.  I think that the devs hit the nail on the head when it comes to capturing some of the old Guantlet style of play and sort of adding a modern feel to it of sorts.   The asking price isn't bad for what you get."
