,Recommended,258970,12225317,"Posted: 24 September, 2014",all,HUNK,"This game looks and runs great, and is a faithful recreation of the original series.All of that is very fortunate, since they completely left out any semblance of RPG elements, which is a real shame, because this game could have been EVEN better with just a moderate amount of thought and effort in that department.What I mean by that is that unlike pretty much every gauntlet game since the N64 version, this game does not have any kind of stats that define the classes.  They might vary slightly in speed/health/damage/etc, but it's all hidden in the game's files, and never sees the light of day as far as the player is concerned.That also means there's no real leveling system.  The mastery system _somewhat_ mitigates this, and does provide very useful bonuses, but it's so achievement-based that it feels insulting to say that it can replace a real RPG system.I was further dismayed when I discovered that the various armors/weapons available for purchase also have no bearing on the gameplay - purely cosmetic.The available relics are respectably varied, but are still a pretty thin replacement for a fleshed-out stat system.That being sad, the combat is utterly solid, and the coop elements support this and vice versa in a very well-thought out manner.  It's just sad that the developers decided not to increase the depth of the game with RPG elements and other mechanics that could continue to keep players engaged for longer.As stated by many other reviews, this game's difficulty level is high.  Hard is definitely hard, even with a group of veteran gamers on teamspeak (and mostly sober), and unfair is duly named.I'd highly recommend to any fan of the series, action ""RPG""s in general, and especially if you have a couple friends you can play it with.  Good $ value."
