76561198048390745,Recommended,258970,12262269,"Posted: 27 September, 2014",all,Ravenwing88,"Gauntlet is infamous to many old-school gamers. A four-player co-operative/competitive adventure in the dungeons, it's seen it's fair share of versions, from the original on the NES, to Gauntlet Legends on the Dreamcast and even further to Seven Sorrows on PS3 and Xbox 360.  But out of all of them, I respect this version the most. One rule that's vital to adhere to is a half-begrudging friend system. Share your food with your allies to keep them alive (or destroy it when they need it if you REALLY don't like them), but under no circumstances can you share your gold. Trust me, they wouldn't for you. It's a system that even best friends stick to, you CAN'T share gold, so while you're working together with your friends, you may be surprised to realise you're also planning for their demise or the next way you can steal gold from them.This is a fantastic revamp of a legendary game, Highly recommended."
