76561197979353861,Not Recommended,258970,12340288,"Posted: 3 October, 2014",all,Ghostlight,"I can;t recommend this game. Despite it being really fun to begin with and with some great-feeling intense combat, at the end of the day, this is NOT Gauntlet. The main problems with the game are as follows:1) The game is VERY short. 30-odd levels, most of which are VERY small and very similar - it will take you a mere 4 hours to see the entire game2) The levels are 100% linear - you move from one rectangular area to next, and you are stuck in each till you clear it; additionally, the keys you need are pretty much lying right beside the locked door :/ There is zero exploration here3) There is almost zero replay value once you complete the game4) Horrible class balance....the Warrior stinks, Wizard is OP noob mode etc etc - maybe deliberate?At the end of the day this should be a 5 or 10 dollar game, as you don't get very much for your buck. Really fun, but only for 4 hours."
