76561198007359627,Not Recommended,258970,35417259,Posted: 2 October,all,Tyson,"I picked up this version Gauntlet hoping to replay some of the great memories of Gauntlet: Legends or Gauntlet: Dark Legacy. Unfortunately I was underwhelmed. In my opinion the developers have taken an extraordinarily simple game and made it unnecessarily complicated. Not that the game isverycomplicated, justunnecessarily so. The game isn't bad, but it is not as easy to pick up an play as I remember it being.For example: the Wizard(""is about to die!"")used to be a ranged spell-chucker. He sat out of reach, and hurled magic balls at the enemies, and you hurt your hands trying to shoot out as many as possible in a given time.Now the Wizard has (count it)nine different spell typeswhich vary in range, casting time, and strength; and good luck remembering which one is which. Again, this isn't a bad mechanic in and of itself, but it isn't reminiscent of the arcade style of play that Gauntlet is famous for.Now, take this with a grain of salt. I haven't logged a huge amount of time in this game, and maybe I'm judging this a bit too harshly due to misguided nostalgia. These are only my opinions, but I didn't feel like this played like an arcade game of yesteryear."
