,Not Recommended,258970,27117894,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,Bustrodux,"Though the game is completely fantastic it's also quite horrible.!!!NOTICE!!! this is essentially a first impression based off the first 5 levels !!!NOTICE!!!Unfortunately i can't bring myself to giving this game an unbiased opinion upon comparing it to the older ones. i'm sorry, but i was misinformed about the game by people saying that it's just like the classics. though yes the description says ""completely new experience!"" i did question it, but was told that that was nothing to worry about and part of what made the game better, which ended up making the game more interesting rather than ""better"".-so you can change how your characters look and with said changes your abilities change with them but i wish you could be able to buy an item, and individually select which item and skill you wanted to use-Turbo bar has been removed and replaced with skills. though this brings newer ways to play the game i do miss being to use up the entire turbo bar to do a badass ultimate like skill-A lot of the exploration seems to be missing and replaced with jump pad like platforms and cracked walls which can only be broken by putting and explosive barrel in front of it, which can be blown up beforehand so you miss out on exploration because you made a stupid mistake rather than failing to do some secret stuff in a specific way-Death is no longer killable with skills and potions, instead you now have to run away from it until it temporarily disappears-any explosion, whether it be from barrels, skills, or potions all seem to do diddly squat-Monster Generators stay the same and always send out the same enemies through its entire lifespan + instead of being big, medium, small, dust they have a health bar and if you're melee (read below) you're pretty much guaranteed to lose some HP trying to take it down unless you sit back and let the ranged classes do the work-keys, potions, and food are no longer randomly findable items as well as there being enough keys for you in every level to open all locks, and only one type of potion-characters now have full lines when talking and they interact with what's going on and what they do such as eating food when on super low health, or another character dieing-has that hack and slash gameplay but that beat-em-up feel to itThe single most cancer mechanic of the game that caused multiple problems: (if you read this and decide to tell me to just not use a controller, you're a ♥♥♥♥ing heretic)-Valkyrie and Warrior are now melee: they try to make for the loss by giving them more health but that doesn't matter because you still have to keep your distance from the swarming amounts of enemies. not just that but i feel like i'm being forced to use a keyboard + mouse or get a trickshot controller because the claw method forces you to miss things completely. for instance, the valkyrie starts with a shield that can be thrown but guess what, the right thumbstick is to aim and the left thumbstick is to move, SO if i want to throw my shield at enemies meanwhile running away i have to take my right thumb off the thumbstick to press B, BUT since my character is running in the opposite direction and i'm no longer aiming the game just naturally makes the character turn in the direction that i'm running and throws the shield in said direction instead. but don't worry Archers and Wizards are excluded from such a thing, BECAUSE they automatically do their basic attack in the direction that they're aiming which the Valkyrie, dunno bout the Warrior, DOES NOT HAVE.Now why would you do this? D:-Archer is no longer femaleNo matter what you gotta give em credit for this-food can still be destroyed + the game calls out the person who did it XD"
