76561198017146983,Not Recommended,258970,18738744,"Posted: 28 October, 2015",all,majdi7,"I never write reviews for anything but this game was so bad, so heart wrenchingly dissapointing, that it's going to get a horrible review. As a kid, I loved the original NES Gauntlet. Before this game was released, I was itching to get the game. I bought it only to find out I could not run it on XP. I planned buying an entire new computer just so I could finally play this game. After getting to Windows 10 and finally playing this game, here are the fundamental horrible injustices of the game.1. It's a grinding game. We finished the campaign on normal difficulty and barely have enough gold to buy 1 relic let alone upgrade it to level 2 (max is 3). There are 8 relics, 5 weapons, 3 talisman. Then there is a bunch of wardrobe stuff that is expensive and does nothing to help you. Of all the relics and weapons and talisman, you can only equip one of each category and the default seems to be the best. The descriptions are terrible so you don't know what you get until after you buy it and it's not refundable. So... fine, let's just play the game like the original... except even the achievements for the game, ""Kill 50,000 bad guys"" is just unreasonable. We finished the game and I haven't reached 2000 bad guys. And all of this is PER CHARACTER. To put it in sperspective, 9 hours = 2000 bad guys then do that 5 more tmes. I bought the DLC pack to get the new Necromancer and this game is so terrible, I don't want to even try it out.2. There is a terrible audio bug that completely crashes Windows. Windows 7, 8, and 10 have experienced it. First you lose audio completely in game, then Skype, then completely. Reboot fixes it... if you can reboot... This made everyone I play with rush for the uninstall button which is now totalling 5 players.3. Gauntlet didn't have much of a plot but the original 8-bit Nintendo had more plot than this game. The commentary is so cringeworthy that NAVI from Zelda 64 seems less annoying and makes problem 2 seem like a blessing.4. The worst part of the game is the actual game play. Bad guys spawn at a rate faster than you can kill them and you just get swarmed. Cool down abilities are too long, bad guys are over powered, and bad guys can shoot through obstacles and do 90% if not 100% damage in 1 hit. Food and Potions from the original game have really lost their value completely.This game is so terrible that I honestly would like a refund for the game. I truly regret this purchase."
