,Not Recommended,258970,19634272,"Posted: 11 December, 2015",all,KrudlerTheHorse,"This game is indeed true to it's arcade roots and represents a great way to have up to 4 players in a local co-op match.Each of the 4 characters (and a 5th if you pay to unlock it) has a unique method of play, meaning that even in a single-player setting, there should be a degree of replayability.But the killer negative aspect is that the game does not play very well using the Steam Controller.  The Steam Controller's right track pad acts as the ""right joystick"" which is used for power-attacks and it works in combination with the A, B, X, Y buttons.  However the buttons are very difficult to press in conjuction with trackpad, making essential attacks difficult during basic action scenes and essentially impossible when the game gets hectic.If you are using a controller that has an actual physical right-joystick, and not just a trackpad emulating one, this game would probably be worth the minimal cost."
