76561198010209253,Not Recommended,258970,12208295,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,mooncats5,"I was really excited for this game when I first heard about it - my friend and I were playing Hammerwatch together awhile back but were left wanting something a bit more polished and dynamic. So why not just go right to the source, right?I downloaded and played it as soon as it was available... only to find that it's a bit of a glitchy mess. The sound skips when in the actual dungeon areas (everything runs fine on the title screen and in the shop), the frame rate is pretty bad overall (even at the lowest settings), and I've already had the game crash on me after just a few minutes playing through the first area. Furthermore, not only can you not re-map your keys on your keyboard (there are no control options whatsoever), but the game doesn't recognize my controller - forcing me to use an emulator to make it think it's an X-Box controller (though admittedly not that big a deal, it's still kind of annoying. And then I found out my controller is aparently broken. Great.)Speaking of which, the game is pretty hard - but it feels even harder playing with keyboard controls. I can't get used to using Shift for important skills like Dodge Rolling and Wizard Spells... I'd much rather be able to use my number keys or, well, anything else.Another annoyance is accidentally unlocking closed off areas that I didn't mean to all because I was trying to kite enemies on the Elf. Pressing F to open doors would have been nice. Just sayin'.Of what I've played of the game, despite all the rough edges, it seems fun. It's an unforgiving game as well - which is good! I like a bit of difficulty (though I wish the controls didn't factor into it).Overall, you might want to wait for them to patch this game... which I hope they do soon! As it stands it's really, REALLY hard for me to stand playing it for more than 30 minutes. With the sound off, of course."
