,Recommended,258970,17060024,"Posted: 15 July, 2015",all,Gen_Tso,"When it works the way it should, Gauntlet is a great update to a classic game. The different characters offer different play styles, and when combined in co-op complement each other. Each section of levels has a certain style, with different types of enemies and a variety of challenges to keep things interesting. The formula is simple: Kill monsters to progress through dungeons and grab as much gold as you can on the way. Your score for each level goes toward unlocking and upgrading bonus abilities for your character, and you can spend gold to purchase new armor and items to use. The game is a bit short, but has high replay value and is a great way to kill a couple hours with friends. Unfortunately, the game can be buggy as hell. Many people can't get it to run at all, and others have experienced constant crashes and glitches. Keep that in mind before you purchase. You may have to do a little work to get the game to run smoothly, but once you do, there is a lot of fun to be had."
