76561198093253279,Recommended,258970,20202049,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,clocutron,"It may be important to note that I did not play this game before the Slayer Edition update so I can't compare the changes to what the earlier release was like.I have always been a fan of Gauntlet games since playing a ton of the original 4-player co-op arcade game.  My favorites along the way were Gauntlet IV for the Sega Genesis and Gauntlet: Dark Legacy for the PS2.  I feel that this game is a pretty good entry in the franchise.I have completed about 10 hours of play so far and I'm enjoying the game quite a bit.  My system struggled a little with some of the graphics settings but, once I turned some things down, it has played very smoothly while still looking quite good.  I believe that Arrowhead did a good job of recreating the spirit of the original in a modernized version of the game.It's pretty easy to jump right in and start playing because gameplay is quite basic.  The weapon and potion abilities are a nice touch to aid in combat.  Some people have complained about the repetition in environments and enemies but that's been the case with every Gauntlet game - I see that as being true to the franchise.As for negatives, I find that the system for buying new weapons and stuff is lacking.  It's not immediately apparent what benefits, if any, there are to buying upgrades.  Some things seem to do nothing more than change the character's appearance.  Different weapons have different abilities but there's no indication that the weapons are more powerful.  Relics seem interesting but their use is not totally intuitive.  I plan to experiment more to see how useful they might be.Another problem I have is Death.  In previous Gauntlet games, you could use potions to kill Death.  However, in this game it appears that potions simply drive Death away for a short time.  Potions are fairly uncommon and you can only carry a few at a time so you really just have to try to avoid Death, which can be really frustrating.Overall, I find this game to be a lot of fun to play.  I would prefer a better system for buying upgrades and I would like a better way to deal with Death like earlier Gauntlet games but these negatives don't stop the game from being fun.  The $20 full price isn't terrible but I would recommend waiting for a sale if you can."
