,Recommended,258970,15703141,"Posted: 5 May, 2015",all,Skadisson,"All you need is friends, if you have friends you can play with, this game unfolds itself to one of very few games on PC that are on par with Nintendo system games in terms of just having fun with friends and competing against friends while always play together as a team. As some reviews here say it's a short game. You can play the normal difficulty through in two or three sessions, every session one of the 3 chapters with 4 sub-chapters with about 4 stages each, depending on how fast you get the puzzles, more complex bossfights and challenging level designs. So you have about 48 stages that are handcrafted and play and look very differently from each other. This is an arcade style game, it's ment to be played when you happen to find half an hour to have leisure time with friends online. Or if you suddenly all got time on your hand and don't know what to play together: This is the perfect game for that. For singleplayer only or if you want to play through a rich story together, i'd say better get another action RPG like Dungeon Siege 3. And before i forget it: Gauntlet is not easy! It is not an easy game, you need brain, a good overview over hectic situations, the ability to hit with skillshots (everything in this game is a skillshot!) and hence, very fast reactions, even when playing together with up to 3 other players. And you'll need to find a way to make quick decisions together as a team, in some cases you will be punished as a team for deciding for different routes or actions at the same time. A good example is a situation where you have less keys than there are doors to unlock and behind some doors there might be more keys. And the UI? It's the best action RPG UI i've ever seen, that even allows for every player's character information to be completely visible on each player's screen simultaneously! You see all your friend's resources, cooldowns, active spells, etc. The UI and hack'n'slash combat are genious, both on par with Diablo 3, at least!"
