,Recommended,258970,13370185,"Posted: 14 December, 2014",all,JERICHO DREAD™,"To start off, Gauntlet is a pretty fun game. It feels a lot like the older ones in a way but with newer visuals and soun... Now I still enjoy this game and would recomend checking it out. If you like the original feel of Gauntlet, this is for you! However, there're some problems that popped up which I had great fears of before this game even came out. This is because i was more of a fan of Gauntlet Dark Legacy.Gauntlet is far too short. It has twelve dungeons... no more. Each dungeon (excluding the three boss levels) has three levels. There're also only three different locations you visit throughout the game that span accross all dungeons. The lack of variety in enemies and locations gets a bit dull after a while where as Gauntlet Dark Legacy had eight realms with many different locations and enemies... It also had many hidden levels, many bosses, items, and so much more.The other problem that bugged me is the lack of character choice... Gauntlet Dark Legacy had many characters you could unlock. While Dark Legacy had its own problems with each character playing the same, this's not the case here.in short, I do recomend people try this game out. If you liked the original Gauntlet games more, you might like  this one a lot because it plays and feels very much like those. However, if you are expecting the same amount of content as Gauntlet Dark Legacy, then this game is sadly not for you.I've got mixed feelings about this game so it's hard to really say it's the best for everyone. I do hope more content is added in time.This review was written after the release of the Necromancer and collesium update and DLC."
